snippet.textDisplay: Thank you for your prayers you two. My fiance is trying to come home from the military now. My brother, a Navy Vet, was run over by a vehicle on Oct. 8th, 2019 in San Diego. Mom  and I didn't find out about his accident because he didn't have ID on him. His good friend Carlos, was finally able to track me down 2 weeks later on Oct 26th. Of course Mama, and I were in tears and traumatized. The next day on Oct 27th we were begging ticket counter schedulers at Portland International Airport to help us but because it was a Sunday, no one would help us. Mom and I kept trying and hanging in there, finally after so much trying, we found our angel at Southwest Airlines. She helped us to get a plane ticket one way for Mama to San Diego so my brother Gabriel wouldn't be alone in all he has been going through. The next day, Oct 28th was Mom's Birthday.
